%S A392982 1,4,2,3,3,4,3,6,2,3,2,2,3,3,2,1,1,3,1,1,2,5,2,1,3,1,1,4,1,5,3,3,2,2,
%T A392982 3,1,1,3,2,3,6,5,3,1,3,1,3,2,9,3,2,4,2,1,1,3,1,1,2,1,1,2,4,4,6,2,2,3,
%U A392982 2,3,1,1,7,4,1,3,1,1,1,1,4,1,1,1,1,1,1,1,2,1,2,1,5
%N A392982 Run lengths of consecutive increases of prime(n)/n where prime(n) is the n-th prime.
%C A392982 Conjecture: For every positive integer k there exists m with a(m) = k.
%F A392982 a(n) = A079418(n) - A079418(n-1) for n>1.
%e A392982 The first eight values of prime(n)/n are: 2/1 = 2, 3/2 = 1.5, 5/3 = 1.666..., 7/4 = 1.75, 11/5 = 2.2, 13/6 = 2.166..., 17/7 = 2.428..., 19/8 = 2.375.
%e A392982 Since 2 > 1.5, the first run has length 1, so a(1) = 1.
%e A392982 Since 1.5 < 1.666... < 1.75 < 2.2 and then 2.2 > 2.166..., the next run has length 4, so a(2) = 4.
%e A392982 Since 2.166... < 2.428... and then 2.428... > 2.375, the third run has length 2, so a(3) = 2.
%o A392982 (PARI) lista(nn) = my(v=vector(nn, n, prime(n)/n), nb=1, list=List()); for (n=2, nn, if (v[n] > v[n-1], nb++, listput(list, nb); nb = 1);); Vec(list); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Mar 10 2026
%Y A392982 First differences of A079418.
%K A392982 nonn,new
%O A392982 1,2
%A A392982 _Philip Jameson_, Mar 07 2026
